x4freetext: Preliminary data given
CGR-560 Cyclotron
High purity, >99.9%, 6.8 and 12.3 micron thick Rh Foils
Major impurities: 40 ppm Fe, 40ppm Ru, 100 ppm in.
Stacked target technique was used.
Beam current was measured in Faraday cup and also was
monitored by natTi(d,x)48V reaction.
Decay was followed for several weeks to allow
separation of isomeric states and the different
isotopes.
Recoil effect was found to be less than 1%.
12.1 micron high purity Ti foils used
Extended range high purity Ge gamma detector
Low energy high purity Ge gamma and X-Ray det.
Decay curve analysis of the measured
annihilation peaks were applied.
Correction was made for self-absorption in the Rh
foils for X-ray detection.
The uncertainty of the primary beam energy
was +/-0.2 MeV.
The energy attenuation was calculated by using the
polynomial approximation of Andersen and Ziegler.
Total error is given. Main contributing
components are:
Beam intensity                             (3%)
Number of target nuclei                    (5%)
Nuclear data                               (5%)
Detector efficiency               (3-6%)
Peak area and counting statistics(2-10%)
